@page "/"

<PageTitle>Clinical Notes Summarizer</PageTitle>

<h1>Clinical Notes Summarization Dashboard</h1>

<div style="display:flex;gap:24px;align-items:flex-start;">
    <div style="flex:1;max-width:640px;">
        <p>
            AI-powered system that processes clinical notes, extracts key medical insights, and provides
            concise, structured summaries to help clinicians review patient information faster.
        </p>

        <h2>Quick Actions</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Summarize Latest Note</strong> — Generate a clinical summary for the selected note.</li>
            <li><strong>Ask a Question (RAG)</strong> — Ask clinical questions over patient notes using
                Retrieval-Augmented Generation.</li>
            <li><strong>Ingest &amp; Index</strong> — Reprocess legacy notes for embeddings and similarity search.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Speech-to-Text ingestion (Azure Speech-to-Text)</li>
            <li>AI-powered summarization (Azure OpenAI, or locally-hosted models via Ollama integrated with Semantic
                Kernel)</li>
            <li>Medical entity extraction (medications, allergies, diagnoses, vitals)</li>
            <li>Event-driven processing for scalable workflows (MassTransit &amp; RabbitMQ)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Architecture</h2>
        <p>
            Layered architecture: API (ASP.NET Core) → Application (CQRS / MediatR) → Domain (entities &amp; events) →
            Infrastructure (persistence, AI connectors) → Blazor UI.
        </p>

        <h2>Get Started</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Install .NET 9+ and restore packages: <code>dotnet restore</code>.</li>
            <li>Build the solution: <code>dotnet build</code> or use the provided VS Code tasks.</li>
            <li>Configure AI and database connection strings in <code>appsettings.Development.json</code>.</li>
            <li>Run the API and UI from VS Code using the launch configurations or tasks.</li>
        </ol>

        <p style="font-size:0.9em;color:#666;">
            Note: This project may send data to external AI services. Ensure PHI is handled according to your
            organization's compliance and privacy policies. Consider using local models (Ollama) or Key Vault for
            secrets.
        </p>

        <p>
            For more details refer to the project <a href="/README.md">README</a> in the repository root.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div style="flex:0 0 520px;">
        <img src="images/clinicalsummary.png" alt="Clinical notes summarization illustration"
            style="max-width:100%;border-radius:8px;box-shadow:0 8px 20px rgba(2,6,23,0.06);" />
    </div>
</div>
